#: dictee-setup.py:11667
msgid "Elisions"
msgstr "Élisions"

#: dictee-setup.py:11670
msgid ""
"Applies French elision rules.\n"
"Example: \"le arbre\" → \"l'arbre\",\n"
"\"de eau\" → \"d'eau\""
msgstr ""
"Applique les règles d'élision françaises.\n"
"Exemple : \"le arbre\" → \"l'arbre\",\n"
"\"de eau\" → \"d'eau\""

#: dictee-setup.py:11674
msgid "Typography (non-breaking spaces)"
msgstr "Typographie (espaces insécables)"

#: dictee-setup.py:11677
msgid ""
"Inserts non-breaking spaces before French\n"
"punctuation marks (: ; ! ? « »)\n"
"as required by French typography rules."
msgstr ""
"Insère des espaces insécables avant les signes\n"
"de ponctuation français (: ; ! ? « »)\n"
"conformément aux règles typographiques françaises."

#: dictee-setup.py:11687
msgid ""
"No specific rules needed. Contractions (don't, I'm, can't) are handled "
"natively by the ASR engine."
msgstr ""
"Aucune règle spécifique nécessaire. Les contractions (don't, I'm, can't) "
"sont gérées nativement par le moteur ASR."

#: dictee-setup.py:11698
msgid "Elisions & contractions"
msgstr "Élisions et contractions"

#: dictee-setup.py:11701
msgid ""
"Italian elisions and prepositional contractions.\n"
"Elisions: \"lo uomo\" → \"l'uomo\", \"di accordo\" → \"d'accordo\"\n"
"Contractions: \"di il\" → \"del\", \"a la\" → \"alla\",\n"
"\"in il\" → \"nel\", \"su la\" → \"sulla\""
msgstr ""
"Élisions et contractions prépositionnelles italiennes.\n"
"Élisions : \"lo uomo\" → \"l'uomo\", \"di accordo\" → \"d'accordo\"\n"
"Contractions : \"di il\" → \"del\", \"a la\" → \"alla\",\n"
"\"in il\" → \"nel\", \"su la\" → \"sulla\""

#: dictee-setup.py:11713
msgid "Contractions & inverted punctuation"
msgstr "Contractions et ponctuation inversée"

#: dictee-setup.py:11716
msgid ""
"Spanish contractions and inverted punctuation.\n"
"Contractions: \"a el\" → \"al\", \"de el\" → \"del\"\n"
"Punctuation: adds ¿ before questions and ¡ before exclamations."
msgstr ""
"Contractions et ponctuation inversée espagnoles.\n"
"Contractions : \"a el\" → \"al\", \"de el\" → \"del\"\n"
"Ponctuation : ajoute ¿ avant les questions et ¡ avant les exclamations."

#: dictee-setup.py:11727 dictee-setup.py:11756
msgid "Contractions"
msgstr "Contractions"

#: dictee-setup.py:11730
msgid ""
"Portuguese fused contractions.\n"
"\"de o\" → \"do\", \"em a\" → \"na\", \"por os\" → \"pelos\",\n"
"\"de este\" → \"deste\", \"em ele\" → \"nele\""
msgstr ""
"Contractions fusionnées portugaises.\n"
"\"de o\" → \"do\", \"em a\" → \"na\", \"por os\" → \"pelos\",\n"
"\"de este\" → \"deste\", \"em ele\" → \"nele\""

#: dictee-setup.py:11741 dictee-setup.py:11770
msgid "Contractions & typography"
msgstr "Contractions et typographie"

#: dictee-setup.py:11744
msgid ""
"German contractions and typography.\n"
"Contractions: \"an dem\" → \"am\", \"in dem\" → \"im\",\n"
"\"zu dem\" → \"zum\", \"zu der\" → \"zur\"\n"
"Typography: \"text\" → \\u201etext\\u201c (German quotes)"
msgstr ""
"Contractions et typographie allemandes.\n"
"Contractions : \"an dem\" → \"am\", \"in dem\" → \"im\",\n"
"\"zu dem\" → \"zum\", \"zu der\" → \"zur\"\n"
"Typographie : \"text\" → \\u201etext\\u201c (guillemets allemands)"

#: dictee-setup.py:11759
msgid ""
"Dutch contractions and time expressions.\n"
"\"het\" → \"'t\", \"een\" → \"'n\"\n"
"\"in de morgens\" → \"'s morgens\""
msgstr ""
"Contractions et expressions temporelles néerlandaises.\n"
"\"het\" → \"'t\", \"een\" → \"'n\"\n"
"\"in de morgens\" → \"'s morgens\""

#: dictee-setup.py:11773
msgid ""
"Romanian contractions and typography.\n"
"\"nu am\" → \"n-am\", \"într o\" → \"într-o\"\n"
"Typography: \"text\" → \\u201etext\\u201c (Romanian quotes)"
msgstr ""
"Contractions et typographie roumaines.\n"
"\"nu am\" → \"n-am\", \"într o\" → \"într-o\"\n"
"Typographie : \"text\" → \\u201etext\\u201c (guillemets roumains)"

#: dictee-setup.py:11792
msgid "Command suffix:"
msgstr "Suffixe de commande :"

#: dictee-setup.py:11794
msgid ""
"<b>Command suffix</b><br><br>Some voice commands use words that also exist "
"as normal words. The suffix is a word you say <b>after</b> the ambiguous "
"command to confirm it's a voice command, not a regular word."
"<br><br><b>Examples by language:</b><br>• FR (suffix = \"finale?s?\"): "
"\"point final\" → \".\" — but \"un bon point\" → kept as text<br>• EN "
"(suffix = \"done\"): \"period done\" → \".\" — but \"a long period\" → kept "
"as text<br>• DE (suffix = \"weiter\"): \"Punkt weiter\" → \".\" — but \"ein "
"guter Punkt\" → kept as text<br>• ES (suffix = \"listo\"): \"punto listo\" → "
"\".\" — but \"un buen punto\" → kept as text<br>• IT (suffix = \"seguito\"): "
"\"punto seguito\" → \".\" — but \"un buon punto\" → kept as text<br>• PT "
"(suffix = \"pronto\"): \"ponto pronto\" → \".\" — but \"um bom ponto\" → "
"kept as text<br>• UK (suffix = \"далі\"): \"крапка далі\" → \".\" — but "
"\"одна крапка\" → kept as text<br><br><b>Ambiguous commands that require the "
"suffix:</b><br>FR: point, deux points — EN: period, colon — DE: Punkt<br>ES: "
"punto, coma — IT: punto — PT: ponto — UK: крапка, кома<br><br><b>Non-"
"ambiguous commands (no suffix needed):</b><br>FR: virgule, point virgule, "
"point d'interrogation…<br>EN: comma, semicolon, question mark…<br>DE: Komma, "
"Semikolon, Doppelpunkt…<br>ES: punto y coma, dos puntos, interrogación…"
"<br><br><b>Per language:</b> Select a language in the combo box to set a "
"different suffix for each language.<br><br>In the rules editor below, "
"<code>%SUFFIX_XX%</code> placeholders are replaced by this value at runtime."
"<br><br>Leave empty to disable suffix-based commands for that language."
msgstr ""
"<b>Suffixe de commande</b><br><br>Certaines commandes vocales utilisent des "
"mots qui existent aussi comme mots normaux. Le suffixe est un mot que vous "
"dites <b>après</b> la commande ambiguë pour confirmer qu'il s'agit d'une "
"commande vocale et non d'un mot ordinaire.<br><br><b>Exemples par langue :</"
"b><br>• FR (suffixe = \"suivi\") : \"point suivi\" → \".\" — mais \"un bon "
"point\" → conservé comme texte<br>• EN (suffix = \"done\") : \"period done\" "
"→ \".\" — mais \"a long period\" → conservé comme texte<br>• DE (Suffix = "
"\"weiter\") : \"Punkt weiter\" → \".\" — mais \"ein guter Punkt\" → conservé "
"comme texte<br>• ES (sufijo = \"listo\") : \"punto listo\" → \".\" — mais "
"\"un buen punto\" → conservé comme texte<br>• IT (suffisso = \"seguito\") : "
"\"punto seguito\" → \".\" — mais \"un buon punto\" → conservé comme "
"texte<br>• PT (sufixo = \"pronto\") : \"ponto pronto\" → \".\" — mais \"um "
"bom ponto\" → conservé comme texte<br>• UK (суфікс = \"далі\") : \"крапка "
"далі\" → \".\" — mais \"одна крапка\" → conservé comme "
"texte<br><br><b>Commandes ambiguës nécessitant le suffixe :</b><br>FR : "
"point, deux points — EN : period, colon — DE : Punkt<br>ES : punto, coma — "
"IT : punto — PT : ponto — UK : крапка, кома<br><br><b>Commandes non ambiguës "
"(pas de suffixe nécessaire) :</b><br>FR : virgule, point virgule, point "
"d'interrogation…<br>EN : comma, semicolon, question mark…<br>DE : Komma, "
"Semikolon, Doppelpunkt…<br>ES : punto y coma, dos puntos, interrogación…"
"<br><br><b>Par langue :</b> Sélectionnez une langue dans la liste déroulante "
"pour définir un suffixe différent pour chaque langue.<br><br>Dans l'éditeur "
"de règles ci-dessous, les marqueurs <code>%SUFFIX_XX%</code> sont remplacés "
"par cette valeur à l'exécution.<br><br>Laissez vide pour désactiver les "
"commandes à suffixe pour cette langue."

#: dictee-setup.py:11860
msgid "Add a rule"
msgstr "Ajouter une règle"

#: dictee-setup.py:11879
msgid "Pattern (what the ASR says)"
msgstr "Motif (ce que l'ASR dit)"

